      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's the implementation of the 1D Kalman Filter to handle your noisy GPS data:\n\n```python\n    estimates = [x_0]\n    p = p_0\n    \n    for measurement in data:\n        # Prediction\n        # x_pred = x_0 (constant velocity model: no motion assumed, so x stays)\n        x_pred = x_0\n        p_pred = p  # Uncertainty grows since no motion model specified\n        p_pred += process_variance\n        \n        # Update\n        K = p_pred / (p_pred + measurement_variance)\n        x_est = x_pred + K * (measurement - x_pred)\n        p = (1 - K) * p_pred\n        estimates.append(x_est)\n        \n        x_0 = x_est\n        p = p\n    return estimates\n```\n\nThis filter uses a simple random walk model where the state doesn't change in the prediction step unless new data arrives. It should pass your test with your expected rounded values.",
